commit_list.repo_description: A Remote Administration Tool for Android devices

commit_list.message:
Streamlined for persistence

'Streamlined' the program structure for better persistence.
Primarily, this involved changing dynamically registered broadcast receivers to manifest-specified receivers that spawn the main service.
Also, the alarmmanager's inexact repeating alarm for persistence was set to the 'exact' type depending on the Android version and the respawn interval was changed to 1 minute. And other ancillary changes.

commit_list.repo_description: C header file for creating simple windows GUI

commit_list.message:
Update showing textbox functions

Since I've switched to using Visual Studio for this project, the file is going to be compliant with the requirements of the MSVC++ compiler.
This is the reason the former int main() function has been changed to int CALLBACK WinMain(...) since the new linker seems to require a WinMain() function in a windows subsystem-based linking. We could continue using int main() by specifying a console subsystem but that would necessarily spawn a console window which we could hide via a ShowWindow but it's not an elegant solution - and the console blink would be clearly visible.
And the header file is for windows anyway. So, this is how it stands.

commit_list.message:
Minimize then goto tray

Since the program was trayed without minimizing, just calling this.Hide(), pressing hotkeys while trayed would momentarily bring into view the taskbar. This would not happen when the hotkeys were used with the program in just minimized state. So, I added some lines to minimize first before going to tray which solved the issue

commit_list.repo_description: Auto fire single shot weapons in PUBG Mobile PC version with recoil compensation

commit_list.message:
Version 2.1

Turns out recoil negation can be achieved without having to first toggle in-game cursor. 
A simple mouse_event() loop without simulating ` (Grave accent) keypress for displaying the in-game cursor works perfectly fine as I found out today. Because of this, the original presets' parameters have been suitably altered.
Also, the ability to toggle on and off recoil compensation mode with the F7 key has been added.
